<div class="banner">🧬 Genotype Harmonization</div>

# Genotype Harmonization

<div class="stat-box">
The genotype file (CaptureSeq SNP dosage matrix, UpDog-filtered) and the phenotype
files were produced by different pipelines and may have minor differences in sample
ID formatting (e.g. underscores vs hyphens, capitalisation). Both sets of names are
normalised to a canonical uppercase-no-punctuation form before matching, then column
names in the genotype matrix are renamed to exactly match the phenotype NAMEs so
GWASpoly's internal join works correctly.

**Genotypes with no marker data are automatically excluded** — the final sample list
is the intersection of phenotyped and genotyped individuals.
</div>

```{r geno-harmonize}
# ── Load genotype matrix ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Format: rows = SNP markers; cols = samples + 3 header cols (marker, chrom, pos)
# Values: allele dosage 0–4 (tetraploid UpDog calls)
cat("[GENO] Reading genotype matrix — this may take a moment...\n")
G <- data.table::fread(geno_file)
names(G)[1:3] <- c("marker","chrom","pos")
geno_samples <- setdiff(names(G), c("marker","chrom","pos"))
cat("[GENO] Markers:", nrow(G), "| Genotyped samples:", length(geno_samples), "\n")

# ── Normalise IDs for fuzzy matching ─────────────────────────────────────────
# Strips hyphens, underscores, spaces; converts to uppercase
norm_id <- function(x) toupper(gsub("[-_ ]","", stringr::str_trim(x)))

all_pheno <- unique(c(PH_Y1$NAME, PH_Y2$NAME, PH_COMB$NAME))

geno_map  <- tibble::tibble(orig=geno_samples, key=norm_id(geno_samples))
pheno_map <- tibble::tibble(NAME=all_pheno,    key=norm_id(all_pheno))

join_map <- dplyr::inner_join(geno_map, pheno_map, by="key")
cat("[GENO-HARM] Phenotyped:", length(all_pheno),
    "| Genotyped:", length(geno_samples),
    "| Overlap:", nrow(join_map), "\n")

not_genotyped <- setdiff(norm_id(all_pheno), geno_map$key)
cat("[GENO-HARM]", length(not_genotyped),
    "phenotyped genotypes have NO marker data yet — excluded from all GWAS runs.\n")

if (nrow(join_map) < 20)
  stop("FATAL: fewer than 20 overlapping samples. Check ID formats.")

# ── Rename geno columns to match phenotype NAMEs exactly ─────────────────────
for (i in seq_len(nrow(join_map))) {
  data.table::setnames(G, old=join_map$orig[i], new=join_map$NAME[i])
}

final_samples <- intersect(setdiff(names(G), c("marker","chrom","pos")), all_pheno)
cat("[GENO-HARM] Final usable samples:", length(final_samples), "\n")

G_sub    <- G[, c("marker","chrom","pos", final_samples), with=FALSE]
geno_out <- file.path(out_dir, "geno_numeric_tetra.csv")
data.table::fwrite(G_sub, geno_out)
cat("[GENO-HARM] Harmonised genotype file written.\n")
```

